data.title: Nvidia Shares Drop on Report of Google Challenge in AI Chips
data.description: Meta is in discussions to use the chips — known as tensor processing units, or TPUs — in data centers in 2027, according to the Information, which cited an unidentified person familiar with the talks.  Meta also may rent chips from Google’s cloud division next year, the news outlet said.
data.keywords: Google, Bloomberg, Nvidia, Google Cloud, data centers, Meta Platforms Inc
